node.text:
A moody day on one of the BEST ridges in Scotland 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 

Liathach is up there with the finest mountains that Scotland has to offer. One of the three Torridon Giants, its ridge traverse is a favourite among many hikers and mountaineers, with the Am Fas pinnacle section offering fantastic scrambles that always leaving you wanting just a bit more. 

If you’re looking for a sensational ridge traverse with dramatic views that are second to none, head up to Torridon and give this one a go. You won’t regret it! 🙌

Difficulty: Very Hard
Scrambling: Grade 2
Munros: x2 (Spidean a’Choire Lèith & Mullach an Rathain)
Total Distance: 7.25 miles
Total Ascent: 1326m
Time: 7-10 hours

#scotland #munrobagging #mountains #scrambling #hiking #hikinguk #visitscotland #hikingscotland
@talesbyjosh Deal! No sliding off this one, though 😂
Moody indeed, looking forward to get back to Dundonnell soon. Epic frames👏🏽👏🏽👏🏽
Woh, this look epic with those ridge views 🙌
@jack_hellyar cheers, Jack - appreciate the kind words! 🙌
Up to Torridon to do this in June. Can’t wait! ❤️🏔️
I’ve got two failed attempts, due to outrageous weather!  Will try again eventually
